SEC. 2. The following sitios are constituted or converted as barrios in the Municipality of Calabanga, same province, as follows:

The sitios of Buri and Kani単gan into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Camuning;

The sitio of San Francisco into a barrio to be known as the barrio of San Francisco;

The sitio of Sibao into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Sibao;

The sitio of San Pablo into a barrio, to be known as the barrio of San Pablo;

The sitio of Sogoan into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Lugsad;

The sitios of Kinali, Punicon, Sogsogon and Maybayawas into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Pe単ada;

The sitios of Tawang, Inarihan, Binaliw-gote and Quinali into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Fabrica;

The sitios of Malobago and Rena単gan into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Balombon;

The sitios of Pongod, Quehadog and Baunot (Talacop) into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Sta. Rita;

The sitio of Puro into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Sta. Cruz (Quipayo);

The sitios of Balentong, Anahaw, Elelocdo, Que-Olleta, Que-deleon, Panate単gan, Que-Paligid, Gantiio, Gotean and Tambongon into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Balatasan;

The sitios of Pacoyog, Bangko and Bacong into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Deminorog;

The sitios of Queriwa, Quinali, Napotol and Manoknok into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Punta-Tarawal;

The sitio of Lupi-Lupi into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Sogod;

The sitio of Salvacion into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Salvacion;

The sitio of San Bernardino into a barrio to be known as the barrio of San Bernardino;

The sitios of Bigong, Sogod Bigong and Balod into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Bigaas; and

The sitio of Binaliw into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Binaliw;

SEC. 3. The following sitios are constituted or converted as barrios in the municipality of Canaman, same province, to wit:

The sitio of Cogon into a barrio to be known as the barrio of Teresita;

The sitio of Gotob into a barrio to be known as the barrio of San Agustin;

The eastern half of the barrio of Tacolod into a barrio to be known as the barrio of San Vicente Ferrer;

The eastern half of the barrio of San Jose and the sitio of Calambog into a barrio to be known as the barrio of San Jose East; and

The western half of the barrio of San Jose as the barrio sitio of Bencay into a barrio to be known as the barrio of the San Jose West.

SEC. 4. The Sitios of Kilantaao, Calancaan, Waquit, Ca-talotoan and Tarobog in the Municipality of Sagnay, same province, are constituted into a barrio of said municipality to be known as the barrio of Kilantao.

SEC. 5. This Act shall take effect upon its approval.

Enacted without executive approval, June 21, 1959.
